thread.title: BRIEF-Interactive Brokers Group Reports 903,000 DARTS In March, Up 39% From Prior Year

title: BRIEF-Interactive Brokers Group Reports 903,000 DARTS In March, Up 39% From Prior Year
text:
April 2, 2018 / 4:29 PM / Updated 12 minutes ago BRIEF-Interactive Brokers Group Reports 903,000 DARTS In March, Up 39% From Prior Year Reuters Staff 1 Min Read 
April 2 (Reuters) - Interactive Brokers Group Inc: 
* INTERACTIVE BROKERS GROUP REPORTS BROKERAGE METRICS AND OTHER FINANCIAL INFORMATION FOR MARCH 2018, INCLUDES REG.-NMS EXECUTION STATISTICS 
* 903 THOUSAND DAILY AVERAGE REVENUE TRADES FOR MARCH, 39% HIGHER THAN PRIOR YEAR AND 11% LOWER THAN PRIOR MONTH 
* FOR MARCH, ENDING CLIENT EQUITY OF $129.2 BILLION, 33% HIGHER THAN PRIOR YEAR 
* ENDING CLIENT CREDIT BALANCES FOR MARCH OF $46.9 BILLION, 7% HIGHER THAN PRIOR YEAR AND 1% LOWER THAN PRIOR MONTH 
* 517,000 CLIENT ACCOUNTS IN MARCH, 28% HIGHER THAN PRIOR YEAR AND 2% HIGHER THAN PRIOR MONTH Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:
